The MS. is evidently mutilated, but the statement on fol. 19, col. 3, quoted above is not true, for of the 54 questions there said to be wanting, several are found here, as for example: utrum res conservantur a Deo, utrum virgo corrupta corde sed non corpore babeat aureolam, and others,
